quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  24,44,"It is God Who alternates the night and the day, indeed in these things are an instructive similitude for those who have vision"
  24,45,"And God has created every animate creature from water. Of them there are some that crawl on their bellies, some that walk on two legs, and some that walk on four. God creates what He wills, for indeed God has power over all things"
  24,46,"We have indeed sent down signs that make things manifest, and God guides whom He wills to a way that is straight"
  24,47,"They say, “We believe in God and in the messenger, and we follow them.” But even after that, some of them turn away. They are not really believers"
  24,48,"When they are summoned to God and His messenger, in order that He may judge between them, behold, some of them refuse to come"
  24,49,"But if the truth is on their side, they come to him promptly"
  24,50,"Is it that there is a disease in their hearts, or do they doubt it, or do they fear that God and His messenger will deal unjustly with them? No, they behave wrongfully"
  24,51,"The answer of the believers, when summoned to God and His messenger, in order that He may judge between them, is no thing other than this, they say, “We hear, and we follow.” It is these who will attain felicity"
  24,52,"It is those who follow God and His messenger, and are conscious of God and do right, who will win in the end"
  24,53,"They swear their strongest promises by God, that if only you would command them, they would leave their homes. Say, “Do not make promises, action would be better, and indeed God is well acquainted with all that you do.”"